
# Reflection

This assignment focused on modeling system behavior using state and activity diagrams.
One challenge was determining the correct level of detail to include. Too many states made diagrams complex, 
while too few reduced clarity.

Another challenge was ensuring alignment between diagrams and previously defined requirements and user stories. 
Careful mapping was required to maintain traceability from Assignment 4 and Assignment 6.

State diagrams helped illustrate how system objects change over time, such as assignments moving from creation to completion. 
Activity diagrams, on the other hand, were useful for visualizing workflows like adding assignments and receiving reminders.

Overall, this assignment improved understanding of dynamic system modeling and its role in bridging requirements and implementation.
